COM.sootNsmoke.jvm
Interface RuntimeConstants

All Known Implementing Classes:
Disassembler, GenericConstant, Gnoloo, Oolong, ClassFile, Sequence, PrologCompiler, SchemeCompiler
public abstract interface RuntimeConstants

A collection of handy constants for working with class files. Add this class to the implements clause in your class and you will be able to refer to (for example) the void signature as SIG_VOID. instead of RuntimeConstants.SIG_VOID. This class has no methods, so you don't have to worry about implementing them.

The SIG and SIGC_ constants can be used in composing method signatures.

The CONSTANT_ constants are used as tags in the constant pool.

The ACC_ constants are used in composing the access flags for fields and methods.

The opc_ constants are opcodes. opcNames translates constants to their names. opcLengths says how long each constant is. (The value is not useful for variable-length instructions).
